children.subject: 61B usually has recorded lectures which you can watch later so you can consider it yes, it can be done asynchronously?

history.content:
Hi,

As I understand, CS 61B allows time conflict enrollment for Spring 2021. However, it is not explicitly listed as asynchronous on the Berkeley Academic Guide.

Is CS 61B asynchronous then? 

That is to say, can I enroll in a lab that partially overlaps with 61B lecture on one of the days (either Monday or Wednesday) without losing credit / missing out on material?

Thank you!
